title: Hillside Hideaway
description: Rustic Private Cottage w/ King Bed + Oceanside View

reviews.comment: This is by far the best airbnb of all time! The space was so unique and artfully designed

full_description: Located in Wills Point, this is a cozy cottage that was originally a church in the early 1900’s. It has original floors, full kitchen and tons of country charm. We are a working farm, so expect chickens pecking around the yard, our big Great Pyrenees Moose meeting you at the drive, and the horse begging for some treats! There is a cozy fire pit out back and you also have a private driveway entrance with covered boat parking available upon request. The cottage features two large bedrooms with walk-in closet, full kitchen with appliances and a nice bathroom with bathtub/shower combo. The living room has a queen sized sofa bed. The decor is country cute and cozy. The bedroom is very spacious with a television located in the armoire, as well as a large HD Roku TV in the living room.

title: The Glenn
description: Enjoy Sunsets at Fully Equipped 2BR Condo

reviews.comment: The pictures really do not do this place justice. It was a stunning home. The home, the property, and the location are all beautiful!

full_description: The apartment is on third floor with a 25 m2 terrace. Panoramic view of the entire city. It has three bedrooms, the largerst with AC and the other two with fans. To access the house it is necessary to use the stairs, but undoubtedly the view is worth every step. Our apartment has 24 hours hot and cold water, Internet connection by prepaid cards from ETECSA with cell phone or laptop from any place in the apartment. Our location allows guests to quickly access both the Historic district and downtown. Cafes, supermarkets, shops and nightclubs are very near us.

title: Moose Haven Cabin
description: Enjoy Secluded Cabin w/ Deck Jacuzzi

reviews.comment: Everything you need for a perfect cabin getaway. They have thought of everything you could possibly need.

full_description: The location is ideal for getting off the grid and enjoying private trails for hiking, biking and snowshoe. The location is remote and beautiful. The Moose Haven is at about 9000 feet along the Park Range in the Rocky Mountains. The heat is furnished by a wood stove that does require stoking through cold nights. The composting bathroom is 20 feet away and the shower house a short walk. Water is supplied as the Moose Haven is a dry cabin. The remoteness, views, ability to have pets make this spot special. There is lots of Timothy Grass for horses, llamas or alpacas. Hiking, biking, xc ski or snowshoe opportunities right from your cabin to our Elk Run Trail or into Forest. Downstairs is a full and twin bed and a queen fold out sofa bed upstairs. There isn't running water in the cabin however well water is provided.
